---HEADER---
file:                  tooling/_validate_symbols.py
language:              python
role:                  Per-SYMBOL validation. Walks one SYMBOL block
                       and emits Findings for missing required fields
                       (kind, pure, total, latency-budget, fragility),
                       bad enum tokens, missing fragility-note when
                       fragility >= medium, missing business-rule for
                       test-layer SYMBOLs, and effects/tests subfield
                       completeness. Pulled out of _validate_island.py
                       so each file stays under the file-size rule.
layer:                 io
status:                verified
confidence:            high (rationale: tests cleanly across all 8 mix
                       islands after rc8 split; no behavior change
                       from the merged version)
generation-pass:       false
read-reason:           task-driven
last-verified:         v0.3-rc8-2026-05-07
maintained-by:         llm
exports:
  - iter_symbol_blocks
  - validate_one_symbol
imports:
  - re
  - pathlib                   :: Path
  - tooling._enums            :: BOOL_ENUM, FRAGILITY_ENUM, SYMBOL_KIND_ENUM
  - tooling.types             :: Finding
depends-on:
  - tooling/_validate_island.py :: imports both exports, calls them once
                                    per SYMBOL block during island
                                    validation
translation-boundary:  none
dynamic-boundary:      false

---SYMBOLS---

SYMBOL: iter_symbol_blocks
kind:           function
pure:           true
total:          true
latency-budget: <10ms per island
effects:
  reads:    none
  mutates:  none
  allocs:   list of (lineno, sub-block) tuples
  throws:   never
  async:    false
  io:       none
called-by:
  - _validate_island.validate_island :: SYMBOL section iteration
calls:
  - re.match
expects:
  - symbols_block is the raw SYMBOLS slice as list[(lineno, line)]
runtime-dependencies:
  - none
tests:
  unit:       none yet
  regression: rc8 smoke test
  security:   none
business-rule: N/A
fragility:    low
fragility-note: N/A

SYMBOL: validate_one_symbol
kind:           function
pure:           false (mutates findings list)
total:          true
latency-budget: <50ms per SYMBOL
effects:
  reads:    none (operates on the symbol block)
  mutates:  the findings list passed in
  allocs:   intermediate match objects, value dicts
  throws:   never
  async:    false
  io:       none
called-by:
  - _validate_island.validate_island :: once per SYMBOL block
calls:
  - re.match
  - the enum_token callable injected from _validate_island
expects:
  - block is the SYMBOL's slice
  - layer is the island's HEADER.layer (used to require business-rule
    on test-layer SYMBOLs)
  - enum_token is the function from _validate_island
  - findings is a mutable list of Finding
runtime-dependencies:
  - none
tests:
  unit:       none yet
  regression: rc8 smoke test
  security:   none
business-rule: N/A
fragility:    medium (rationale: many enum / required-field branches;
                                  format changes cascade)
fragility-note: enum_token is injected as a parameter to avoid a
                circular import (_validate_island imports this file;
                cannot also import a helper FROM this file's parent
                without cycles). When refactoring, preserve the
                injection.

---RISKS---

security:                none
regression-sensitivity:
  - SPEC/02_SYMBOLS.md changes to required SYMBOL fields cascade here
  - changes to effects/tests subfield names (currently 6 + 3) cascade
  - any change to fragility or kind enum membership must update
    tooling/_enums.py first
platform-sensitivity:    none
config-dependencies:     none

---MEMORY---

ACTIVE-CONSTRAINTS:
  - id: AC-001
    constraint:  enum_token is INJECTED, not imported. Keep it that
                 way to avoid circular imports.
    established: 2026-05-07
    evidence:    HD-001

HISTORICAL-DECISIONS:
  - id: HD-001
    decision:  enum_token is passed as a parameter, not imported
    reason:    _validate_island.py imports this module; if this
               module also imported enum_token from _validate_island,
               that would be a circular import. Passing enum_token
               as a parameter keeps the import graph one-way.
    date:      2026-05-07
    outcome:   stable
    evidence:  inferred-from-design

SUPERSEDED:
  - none yet
